               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-338-person2338">
                  SIMON 
                  JACQUES ROCHARD
               <interp inst="t18310630-338-person2338" type="surname" value="JACQUES ROCHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-338-person2338" type="given" value="SIMON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-338-person2338" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18310630-338-viclabel1776" type="occupation">miniature-painter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-338-victim2337 t18310630-338-viclabel1776"></join>, and live in Regent-street. On the evening of the 1st of<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183106300146"></xptr>July I was walking in <placeName id="t18310630-338-crimeloc1777">Argyle-place</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-338-crimeloc1777" type="placeName" value="Argyle-place"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-338-crimeloc1777" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-338-off1774 t18310630-338-crimeloc1777"></join>, a little before eight o'clock - I heard a cry of Stop thief! and saw Hobbs running after the prisoner; I had felt my coat pocket moving, and missed my handkerchief, which I had safe the minure before - I afterwards received it from a gentleman who saw it on the ground, and ran after me with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-338-person2339">
                  THOMAS 
                  HOBBS
               <interp inst="t18310630-338-person2339" type="surname" value="HOBBS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-338-person2339" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-338-person2339" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. On the evening of the 1st of July, I saw the prisoner in Regent-street, in company with another person; I saw him follow different gentlemen, and attempt their pockets - I followed him on to Argyle-place, and saw him put his hand into the prosecutor's pocket; he drew it out without the handkerchief - he put it in a second time, and brought out the handkerchief; I instantly went towards him - I suppose he saw me, and threw the handkerchief on the pavement - he and his companion then separated; I pursued, and took him in Regent-street - I had not lost sight of him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going along Argyle-street- a boy picked a gentleman's pocket, and ran by me; I crossed the road - the Policeman pursued the boy; he run too fast for him - he then turned and took me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310630-338-verdict1778" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310630-338-verdict1778" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 9.</p>
